<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<knowl mode="exercise" xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">
        <intro>
            <p>
                Solve the following integrals using partial fraction decomposition and substitution when appropriate. 
            </p>
            <!--<p>
                (If an open circle appears on an point which is not a jump discontinuity, ignore it.)
            </p>-->
        </intro>

        <knowl>
            <content>
                <p>
                    <m>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \int \frac{ {{num}} }{ {{denom}} } dx</m>.


                </p>


            </content>
            <outtro>
                <p>
                  Since
                    <me>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \frac{ {{num}} }{ {{denom}} }  = {{PF}} </me>
                  We have that   
                  <m>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \int \frac{ {{num}} }{ {{denom}} } dx = \int \left( {{PF}} \right)dx = {{Fx}} +C </m>.
                </p>


            </outtro>
        </knowl>

        <knowl>
            <content>
                <p>
                    <m>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \int {{f2x}}dx</m>.


                </p>


            </content>
            <outtro>
                <p>
                    By letting <m>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} u={{U}}</m>, we have that 
                    <m>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \int {{f2x}}dx = {{F2x}}+C.</m>
                </p>


            </outtro>
        </knowl>
    
    
        
    
    
    
    
    
   
    
   
</knowl>
